{"pii": "S0981942823003765", "abstracts": {"#name": "abstracts", "$": {"xmlns:ce": true, "xmlns:dm": true, "xmlns:sb": true}, "$$": [{"#name": "attachments", "$$": [{"#name": "attachment", "$": {"xmlns:xocs": true}, "$$": [{"#name": "attachment-eid", "_": "1-s2.0-S0981942823003765-ga1.jpg"}, {"#name": "ucs-locator", "_": "https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/prod-ucs-content-store-eu-west/content/pii:S0981942823003765/ga1/DOWNSAMPLED/image/jpeg/73a0c0bfc618e19aa33e83290ea5495b/ga1.jpg"}, {"#name": "file-basename", "_": "ga1"}, {"#name": "abstract-attachment", "_": "true"}, {"#name": "filename", "_": "ga1.jpg"}, {"#name": "extension", "_": "jpg"}, {"#name": "filesize", "_": "110410"}, {"#name": "pixel-height", "_": "194"}, {"#name": "pixel-width", "_": "500"}, {"#name": "attachment-type", "_": "IMAGE-DOWNSAMPLED"}]}, {"#name": "attachment", "$": {"xmlns:xocs": true}, "$$": [{"#name": "attachment-eid", "_": "1-s2.0-S0981942823003765-ga1.sml"}, {"#name": "ucs-locator", "_": "https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/prod-ucs-content-store-eu-west/content/pii:S0981942823003765/ga1/THUMBNAIL/image/gif/ae941b83e62d77c17e723188320c72b4/ga1.sml"}, {"#name": "file-basename", "_": "ga1"}, {"#name": "abstract-attachment", "_": "true"}, {"#name": "filename", "_": "ga1.sml"}, {"#name": "extension", "_": "sml"}, {"#name": "filesize", "_": "75935"}, {"#name": "pixel-height", "_": "85"}, {"#name": "pixel-width", "_": "219"}, {"#name": "attachment-type", "_": "IMAGE-THUMBNAIL"}]}, {"#name": "attachment", "$": {"xmlns:xocs": true}, "$$": [{"#name": "attachment-eid", "_": "1-s2.0-S0981942823003765-ga1_lrg.jpg"}, {"#name": "ucs-locator", "_": "https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/prod-ucs-content-store-eu-west/content/pii:S0981942823003765/HIGHRES/image/jpeg/a66954950f8e242d4918c154e91ddcdb/ga1_lrg.jpg"}, {"#name": "file-basename", "_": "ga1"}, {"#name": "abstract-attachment", "_": "true"}, {"#name": "filename", "_": "ga1_lrg.jpg"}, {"#name": "extension", "_": "jpg"}, {"#name": "filesize", "_": "501890"}, {"#name": "pixel-height", "_": "859"}, {"#name": "pixel-width", "_": "2213"}, {"#name": "attachment-type", "_": "IMAGE-HIGH-RES"}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"lang": "en", "id": "abs0010", "view": "all", "class": "author"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "sectitle0010"}, "_": "Abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abssec0010", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "abspara0010", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "__text__", "_": "Plants involve a fine modulation of pectin methylesterase (PME) activity against microbes. PME activity can promote the cell wall stiffening and the production of damage signals able to induce defense responses and plant resistance to pathogens. However, the molecular mechanisms underlying PME activation during disease remain largely unknown. In this study, we explored the role of subtilases (SBTs) as PME activators in Arabidopsis immunity. By using biochemical and reverse genetic approaches, we found that the expression of SBT3.3 and SBT3.5 influences the induction of defense-related PME activity and resistance to the fungus "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "Botrytis cinerea."}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " Arabidopsis "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "sbt3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " and "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "sbt3.5"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " knockout mutants showed decreased induction of PME activity and increased susceptibility to the fungus. "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "SBT3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " expression was stimulated by oligogalacturonides. Overexpression of "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "SBT3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " overactivated PME activity during fungal infection and enhanced resistance to "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "B. cinerea"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": ". A negative correlation was observed between "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "SBT3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " expression and cell wall methyl ester content in the genotypes analyzed after "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "B. cinerea"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " infection. Increased expression of defense-related genes, including "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "PAD3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": ", "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "CYP81F2"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " and "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "WAK2"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": ", was also revealed in "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "SBT3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " overexpressing lines. We also demonstrated that SBT3.3 and pro-PME17 are both secreted into the cell wall using distinct protein secretion pathways and different kinetics. Our results propose SBT3.3 and SBT3.5 as modulators of PME activity in Arabidopsis against Botrytis to promptly boost immunity limiting the growth-defense trade-off."}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"class": "graphical", "id": "abs0015", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "sectitle0015"}, "_": "Graphical abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abssec0015", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "abspara0015", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "display", "$$": [{"#name": "figure", "$": {"id": "undfig1"}, "$$": [{"#name": "alt-text", "$": {"role": "short", "id": "alttext0010"}, "_": "Image 1"}, {"#name": "link", "$": {"xmlns:xlink": true, "locator": "ga1", "type": "simple", "role": "http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4", "href": "pii:S0981942823003765/ga1", "id": "aep-link-id12"}}]}]}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"class": "author-highlights", "lang": "en", "id": "abs0020", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "sectitle0020"}, "_": "Highlights"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "abssec0020", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "abspara0020", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list", "$": {"id": "ulist0010"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "u0010"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "p0010", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "__text__", "_": "The expression of "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "SBT3.3"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " is induced by pectin-related DAMPs (Damage Associated Molecular Patterns)."}]}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "u0015"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "p0015", "view": "all"}, "_": "SBT3.3 and SBT3.5 contribute to the activation of defence-related PMEs and Botrytis resistance."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "u0020"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "p0020", "view": "all"}, "_": "SBT3.3 influences the expression of specific defense genes and the structure of pectin against Botrytis."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "u0025"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "p0025", "view": "all"}, "_": "SBT3.3 is secreted via Exocyst Positive Organelles (EXPOs) in the apoplast where it colocalizes with Pro-PME17."}]}]}]}]}]}]}}